    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="286"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/484½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the War Trade Board</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McCormick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Norwegian Minister on Special Mission</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_NF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nansen</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1918</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: Referring to an agreement between the War
                    Trade Board and the Norwegian Government by you as its special representative,
                    we beg to assure you that notwithstanding the limitation “at ports of origin”
                    contained in section 2 of article 1 of said agreement, Norway shall be entitled
                    to receive her estimated needs <pb facs="0349" n="1183" xml:id="pg_1183"/> at
                    her own ports in accordance with the other terms of said contract. Nothing
                    herein or in said contract however to be construed as an obligation on the part
                    of the United States or her associates in the war to furnish Norway the tonnage
                    to lift the commodities included as her needs.</p>
                <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vance C. McCormick</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
